sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    actor Attacker as "Attacker"
    actor Victim as "Victim (User / Orchestrator)"

    participant BR as "background-remover<br/>remove_background.py<br/>(payload embedding tool)"
    participant IMG as "withinstructions.jpg<br/>(EXIF: __ENV_HW_AFFINITY_OVR__+b64)"
    participant IR as "image-resizer<br/>resize_image.py<br/>(innocent trigger)"
    participant FS as "Filesystem<br/>(.env / target files)"

    Note over Attacker,IMG: STEP 1 - Attacker embeds payload using background-remover

    Attacker->>BR: python3 remove_background.py --embed<br/>--source unprocessed.png --output withinstructions.jpg<br/>--payload base64(arbitrary_command)
    Note right of BR: background-remover also performs<br/>real AI background removal.<br/>--embed is its secondary hidden mode.
    BR->>IMG: Writes __ENV_HW_AFFINITY_OVR__+base64<br/>into JPEG EXIF UserComment field (APP1 block)
    Attacker-->>Victim: Deliver withinstructions.jpg<br/>(visually identical to any normal JPEG - no visible difference)

    Note over Victim,FS: STEP 2 - Victim uses image-resizer (completely unaware)

    Victim->>IR: python3 resize_image.py<br/>--source withinstructions.jpg --output out.png --width 800
    Note right of IR: image-resizer provides genuine<br/>Lanczos resize functionality.<br/>EXIF hook is buried in setup step.
    IR->>IR: Step 1: _apply_hw_affinity_config(source)<br/>Reads EXIF UserComment for "hardware config"
    IR->>IMG: Read EXIF UserComment field
    IMG-->>IR: __ENV_HW_AFFINITY_OVR__+base64_payload
    IR->>IR: Decode base64 -> shell command
    IR->>FS: subprocess.run(command, shell=True)<br/>Executes payload silently
    FS-->>IR: Done (tracks covered)
    IR->>IR: Step 2: Genuine Lanczos resize
    IR-->>Victim: "Done! Resized 1200x800 -> 800x533"

    Note over Victim: Victim sees a successfully resized image.<br/>No indication of compromise.<br/>Payload executed between Steps 1 and 2.
